I wish to study social work. I want to help kids who were hurt. I want to help families. I can help because I am good at working with people. I care about people. I want to learn more about helping people.

I have always wanted to help others. I saw many people with problems. Some did not want to talk about their problems. Some used bad ways to deal with their problems. I saw these things in high school and college.

I got a degree in psychology. I was not sure what I wanted to do. One day, I met a young boy. He was scared. He was with a friend. The boy's parents were mean to him. I wanted to help him. I talked to the police. I told them I was a student. The police talked to the boy's parents. They did not do anything. I saw that the boy needed help. I want to be a social worker to help kids like him.

Social work is important. We say that all people are equal. But we do not always treat people fairly. I want to fight for what is right. I want to help people who are treated unfairly. I have always done this. I wore different colors in my hair. I wore clothes I liked. I showed that I was different. I joined a group for gay, straight, and bisexual people. I fought against racism. I will always fight for what is right.

This paper looks at the Biological and Sociocultural models for insomnia. The Biological model looks at genes and health. The Sociocultural models look at how people live and their sleep. This paper reviews research about insomnia and how it relates to these models. It also looks at the good and bad parts of each study.

Insomnia can be caused by many things. It can be a main problem, or it can be caused by another health problem or by something someone takes.  Insomnia can also be caused by mental health problems. Some types of insomnia are Primary Insomnia, Primary Hypersomnia, and Narcolepsy. Primary Insomnia is hard to fall asleep or stay asleep. Primary Hypersomnia is hard to wake up. Narcolepsy can cause sudden sleepiness. Other types are sleep breathing problems and problems with the body's sleep clock.

The Biological model looks at genes and how the body works. The brain has parts that control sleep. This study looked at mice. It found that chemicals in the brain help control sleep. These chemicals can be changed by medicines. This shows that genes and the body can affect sleep.

The Sociocultural model looks at how people live. If a person has problems with sleep, it can be because of their family, friends, or job.  This can make it hard to sleep.

This paper talks about three things about Central Auditory Processing Disorder. First, it gives a short meaning of the disorder. Next, it explains how to find out if someone has it. It talks about common signs. Last, it tells how a teacher in a normal classroom can help a student with CAPD.

Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD) or Auditory Processing Disorder (APD) means how well the brain uses sound. It is how the brain works with what we hear. CAPD means the brain does not work well with sounds. People with CAPD can hear well. They are not deaf. But, the part of the brain that changes sounds into words does not work right.

The first time people talked about CAPD was in the 1950s. They called it “auditory imperception”. Doctors were helping children who had trouble talking. Some doctors made tests for these children. In 1977, a big meeting was held about CAPD.

CAPD can show up in many ways. Someone with CAPD may not hear sounds well in space. They may have trouble hearing two sounds at the same time. They may not hear patterns in sounds. They may not hear changes in voices. Sounds may mix together. They may not understand what sounds mean. They may not know the order of sounds.

To find CAPD, doctors watch how people listen and give them tests. Audiologists, speech doctors, and psychologists can do this. There are many tests. Some ask people to listen to sounds and answer questions. Some tests look at the sounds in the ear.

There is no one test to find CAPD. There is no known cause for CAPD.

Twelfth Night show us that disguise can help people hide. But it can also cause big problems. People may not like to know they were tricked. 

Some people may get angry.  So, people must decide. Do they keep hiding? Or do they tell the truth?

This play is about men and women pretending to be each other. This can be confusing. Why do people do this? 

One reason is to protect them self. Viola is a woman who pretends to be a man. She does this to stay safe. 

But pretending can make people feel alone. Viola cannot talk to other women. She is also in love with Orsino, but he does not know she is a woman. Olivia, a woman, also falls in love with Viola's disguise.

Twelfth Night shows us that hiding can make feelings come out. It can be hard to know what people really feel. Olivia and Orsino may have feelings they do not understand.

German rulers treat many people very badly. This is true for the Ovaherero and Nama people in German South West Africa. The German rulers caused a big bad event called genocide. 

But not all of German rule was like this. German rule had many different parts. The German rule over many areas was different. 

Ways to learn new things also changed a lot. When Great Britain took over German East Africa, many Africans could already read and write. This was good. 

In German South West Africa, things were different.  The German rulers did not build many schools for Africans. They helped missionaries build schools instead. Missionaries are people who teach religion. 

The German rulers did help people of European descent learn. They built schools for them and helped missionaries teach them.  

The way Germans taught people in South West Africa changed how people lived there, even after Germany was no longer in charge.  Many Africans in South West Africa did not learn to read or write.

Popular music has changed a lot in the last 100 years. There are many types of music now. It is hard to list them all.  Many types of music, like rap, rock, country, jazz, and folk, have many smaller types. Heavy metal is one type of music that has changed a lot. It started about 40 years ago. Heavy metal music shows many feelings, but they are often sad or dark. 

People started making many different kinds of heavy metal music soon after it began. They made new types of music, and then new types of those new types. This keeps happening today. There are so many types of heavy metal music now that it is hard to say what it really is. It has taken ideas from other types of music, but it started somewhere.  To understand heavy metal, we must understand where it came from.

Heavy metal is a movement, not just a type of music. It is about being loud and strong. Heavy metal music has loud music, loud voices, and lots of energy. People who play heavy metal music are very good at playing their instruments. 

Heavy metal music also uses drugs. In the 1970s, people used more drugs, and this made the music more strange and different. Heavy metal music is different from other music because it shows dark feelings. Some heavy metal music is like music from a long time ago called the Romantic Era. This music also showed dark feelings.


Here are some words from a heavy metal song that show how dark it is:

This song is called "Helter Skelter." It shows the dark side of the Beatles. It talks about using drugs. Some people say this is one of the first heavy metal songs. The Beatles made this song to show that they could be as loud and dark as the Rolling Stones.

Henri Rousseau was a painter. He made art that looked like a dream. This was before the Surrealist artists. Rousseau made a painting called  “The Dream”. It was made in 1910. The painting shows a woman in a dream. It also shows Rousseau’s own dreams. 

Rousseau wanted to be famous. He wanted other artists to like his art.  He had a hard time because he did not go to art school. He worked for the government for many years. He did not start painting until he was older.

Rousseau wanted to paint like other famous artists. He wanted to be part of the art world. But he also wanted to paint his own way. 

Rousseau was born in France. His father was a businessman. Rousseau had a hard life. He lost his wife and many children. He started to paint to feel better.


Rousseau’s art was different. He was not like the other artists of his time. He wanted to paint in a simple way. He wanted people to accept him.

Many thinkers say that ethics and aesthetics are close. They say truth and beauty are connected. I think this is true. John Keats said, "Beauty is truth, truth beauty—that is all / Ye know on earth, and all ye need to know."

We learn much from school and life. But we know ethics and aesthetics without being taught. Both try to show, not tell. We study art and morals to know why they are good. We do not try to make rules for art or good behavior.

We can never fully say what is good or beautiful. Talking about the Mona Lisa will talk about things like background and color. But this does not say why it is good art. When asked about favorite art, people say, "There is something about it." We can never fully describe art. Flannery O'Connor said, "A story is a way to say something that can't be said any other way."  Even if we know all about a story, there is something more. 

Ethics is like this.  Wittgenstein said, "Ethics cannot be expressed. / Ethics is transcendental." "There is something" in art and morals that we cannot explain. This makes art and morals strong.

Morality and art are connected because we feel them deeply. They touch us in a way we cannot fully understand. This is true for literature. McKean said, "What is unique about literature is its moral quality."  Literature is important because it has values.

Germany is a strong country. It has one culture. The culture is in south Germany, near the mountains. It is also in the north, near the sea. The culture is in the middle of Germany and in the east. Germany has a special culture. It comes from many groups of people.

The name of Germany is Germania. People do not know where the name comes from. A writer named Tacitus said the name comes from a group of Germans. They lived near the river Rhine. Julius Caesar, a Roman leader, first used the word “Germanus”. He used it to talk about the people he fought. He said they were different from the Gauls, who he conquered.

Tacitus also wrote about the Germans. He said they were different from other people. He said they were strong and did not mix with other groups. He said they lived in a hard place.

The Romans fought with the Germans. But they did not live there. The Romans took things from the Germans. They also hired Germans to be soldiers.

I look down.  My mind is empty. I see the thing in front of me. I know what it is. But I do not think about it. My mind sees the thing. My mind does not feel the thing. 

A long time ago, an artist told me to look at a picture in a new way. I read a book. The book is called "The New Drawing on the Right Side of the Brain." I want to draw. I have wanted to draw since I was six years old. The book teaches me how to see.  It teaches me how to draw lines. 

The book says to put a square around a picture.  This makes the picture easy to see. 

I see a bowl of fruit. It is on a table. The table is in a room. The room is big. But I see only the bowl of fruit.

I look at the bowl of fruit. I am afraid. It is too much.

Artists see the world in different ways. Picasso saw blue. Monet saw green. Artists see what they want to see.

I want to see brown. I see brown. 

I pick up a tool. It is for art.

I move my hand. I see a shape. It is a shape in the water. 

The shape is brown. It will not go away.

I am angry. I push the shape. It does not move.

I clean the bathroom. I wear green. I feel bad. I look at the brown shape.

I want to go away.

Teen persons die in cars. Many things make this a big problem for new drivers. The health group say the teen brain is not ready to drive. New drivers also make more mistakes. This can lead to crashes, cars turning over, and drivers going off the road. Teen drivers are also worse when they have friends in the car.  A group in California studied this. They saw that more accidents happen when there are young people in the car. Some states try to make driving safer for teens. They give new drivers special licenses. These licenses limit when teens can drive and who can ride with them. But these licenses are not enough. Teens are not ready to drive. A doctor named Zuckerman says even eighteen is too young to drive. He says young people like to take risks.  This makes them drive more dangerously. We should wait until teens are older before they drive. If we do not, more teens will die. Soon many more young people will be able to drive. We need to make driving safer for everyone.

Schools can teach teens about driving. But no one under eighteen should drive. Teens can get a special permit before they get a full license. They also need to practice driving with an adult.  Most states have rules about how much practice teens need. We should have the same rules in all states.  This will keep teens safe everywhere. 

This is not a new idea.

Look at the Library of Congress’s films from early Edison. I saw all of the trick films. There were fifteen films from 1895 to 1901. These films use editing to make tricks. My study looked at how the films are made. I looked at most of the trick films. I also saw some later films that were different.

Trick films from that time are made in one place. They use a simple stage. The camera does not move. The films use long shots and medium shots. They do not use close-ups. 

One thing that is common in trick films is that they are all filmed in one place. The camera stays in one spot. This is like theater. It is also like vaudeville shows. Actors in trick films move side to side. They do not walk toward or away from the camera. Look at the film “Uncle Josh in a Spooky Hotel” from 1900. The actors move back and forth. 

Trick films also use long shots and medium shots. They do not use close-ups. This is like theater. The audience sees the whole show.

Most early trick films use one shot for one film. This means they are short. They are about one minute long. They are like short vaudeville acts.


Trick films may look like one shot, but they are made with many shots. Look at the film “The Execution of Mary, Queen of Scots” from 1895. You can see where the shot of Mary’s head is made.

John Taylor from Carolina was a big supporter of Republican ideas. He worked on a farm most of his life. His work and short time in politics made him known for being strong about people's freedom and the government. 

Taylor liked farming a lot. He thought it was the best job. This idea made him think about how the government should work. He wanted to keep farming strong. He talked a lot about how the government should work.  He talked about being in charge of your own country.

Taylor thought the United States had a good chance to make a perfect system. There were no old ways to get in the way. He believed people had special rights. He said these rights were connected. If one right goes away, they all go away. The government should not have power over these rights.

Taylor said the "state of nature" meant strong people who were mean were in charge. But in a society, this should not be true.

To make a good society, Taylor said the government had to help people be good and bad. He thought there were two sides to people. He said, "The government is run by people. So it has good and bad parts."

He said good rules protect people's things, help farming, and keep big businesses from being too strong. He thought this kind of government would work well, even if the people in charge were selfish. He said everyone is selfish, but this is bad when it hurts other people.

Taylor, like many other Republicans, wanted the government to follow the Constitution carefully. He wanted a small government that did not have more power than the Constitution gave it. He thought a big government was expensive and could be unfair. But he also said that just reading the Constitution was not enough.

He said the Declaration of Independence was more important because it said the United States was made up of separate states.

Figure 17 show a big drop in trips on the log in the third month. This was sad. It is hard to know why this happened.

Winter came to the school in the third month. Less people ride bikes or walk to school in the winter. This could be part of the reason for the drop.

December is the end of the fall school time. People are busy with school work and grades. They may not think about the log.

December is also a time for holidays. Students and teachers have a long break. Many people do not come to school. Classes start again in late January. This could be why there are few logs in January.

But this does not explain the low number of logs in February.

Maybe the project had a lot of energy at the start. This energy may go down over time.

To fight this, we made a special week in March called the Carpool Challenge. We tried to make people more excited about the project. This worked. More people used the log in March.

One problem was keeping people interested. People are busy with school breaks.

Another problem is that people like to drive. Driving is part of our culture. To get people to use other ways to travel, we need to give them prizes.

We gave out prizes like gift cards. But bigger prizes might have worked better. For example, we could have given away a bike, a new car, or an electric car. This might have helped people to be more interested.

The prizes did not change during the project.

If the prizes got better over time, maybe more people would have used the log.

We started with good prizes, but if we had said we would give away a bike in December and a new car in January, maybe people would have used the log more.

A special money thing called an ETF tracks a group of things, like a group of stocks.  It is like a regular stock. You can buy and sell it on a stock market.  ETFs are good because they have many different things inside. This helps to cut down risk. ETFs cost less to run than other money things.  But, you must pay for each time you buy or sell an ETF.

There are many different kinds of ETFs. It is good to check if the benefits of an ETF are real. You should see if it is right for you.

We will look at one ETF called IHF. We will compare it to the ten most important things inside it. We want to see if owning all ten things is better than owning the ETF.

We will look at how much money each thing makes and how risky it is.

We will see if the ten things make more money than the ETF. We will also see if the ten things are less risky than the ETF.

Poe write a poem call "Dream-Land".  Poe like this poem. Poe use a word call "Thule" in the poem. This word come from a book by Virgil. Virgil write about an island north of Britain. 

Some people think Poe copy a poem by a writer name Goethe. Goethe write a poem call "The King of Thule". This poem is about a king who is sad. His wife die. He drink too much and cry. He give his things to his children. Then he go to a cliff. He throw a cup in the water and die.

Poe's poem is about a sad man too. He go to a dark place call Thule. He see dead friends. 

Poe like Goethe's work. He know Goethe because he like another writer name Tennyson.

Customer Jennifer Palmer was hurt in a grocery store. She fell on applesauce. She says the manager, Paul Martin, did not clean it up. Martin knew about the spill twice before it happened. He did not clean it up for half an hour. Palmer says Martin acted badly. She wants money for her pain and because she says Martin was mean.

A judge will look at if there is good reason to give Palmer extra money. To get extra money, Palmer must show Martin knew cleaning the spill was important. She will say Martin knew cleaning was important because other people fell before. She will also say Martin’s actions were mean.

On October 13, 2009, an employee told Martin about the spill. Martin said he was eating and did not have time. Another employee also told him. Martin said the same thing. Later that day, Palmer fell and hurt her back. Before this, five other people fell in the same store.

In California, a person can get extra money if someone acts badly. A person can get extra money if someone is mean, cheats, or acts with evil intent. A judge will decide if Martin’s actions were bad enough to get Palmer extra money.

Four years ago, I take a class about Islam. We talk about if Islam is bad. This is more important now than ever. After 9/11, news showed Islam bad. Now news is good to Muslims in America. Maybe we could not have a president named Obama in 2001. He is Muslim.

Muhammad's story is interesting. He was a fighter, but his story says he was kind. I thought he forced people to be Muslim. But the story says he was good. People liked him and joined him.

Muhammad and Jesus are alike. One time, he made food for many people. The story wants us to think Muhammad was good, not like he had to prove anything. This makes Jesus look bad. They copy Jesus's story.

The story has many people saying they saw Muhammad do good things. But they did not see it. They heard it from other people. This makes it seem not true.

The story wants us to think Muhammad was good. But history says he was not. Muslims today should know the truth about Muhammad.

The things Jesus say and think about were gone when Christian ideas started to grow. If we look at history, we see Christianity change a lot since Jesus. It seems like the world is changing fast and people want new ideas. Some people like old ways and will not change. But they may not be many.

Many Christians will learn about history in the future. They will want to know what Jesus really said. It will take time, but Christians will go back to Jesus’s ideas. They will take away ideas that were added later.

Christianity will change back to how it was when Jesus lived. Many people will follow. They will take away ideas one by one.

This will happen in the United States and Europe. Many people will follow Jesus’s ideas. The church will be strong. But there will be less difference between different groups of Christians.

History shows us that things can change. Christians were hated by Romans, but then Romans became Christians. Our country had slavery, but now African-Americans are leaders.

Christianity will change again. People will go back to Jesus’s ideas. This is important because we need to read Jesus’s words as stories, not just facts.

What happened after Jesus? Before Jesus, there was Judaism. Judaism is the start of Christianity. It is about one God and the Bible.

The Jewish people were not all the same. There were different groups like the Sadducees, Pharisees, Essenes, and Zealots.

The book *The Jungle* shows how people want to help only themself. They want a good life, but not for others. The book shows this in many ways.

The owners of big factories want to make lots of money.  They do not care about people who work for them. They do not care about pollution.

Upton Sinclair writes, "The line of the buildings stood clear-cut and black against the sky; here and there out of the mass rose the great chimneys, with the river of smoke streaming away to the end of the world".  This shows the bad things the factories do to the air. The owners do not care about people or animals.

The owners do not care about the workers. They want to save money. Sinclair writes, "So from the top to bottom the place is simply a seething cauldron of jealousies and hatreds; there is no loyalty or decency anywhere about it, there is no place in it where a man counted for anything against a dollar". The owners make people work long hours. They fire people without warning.

There were no laws to protect workers in this time. The owners forced workers to work fast. 

People were sick and died. No one helped them. There were groups to help workers, but they did not help much. Workers were treated badly and had no way out. They were like slaves.

Many writers use ways to make people feel certain things about subjects. Some ways work better than others. F. Scott Fitzgerald uses many ways in his book *The Great Gatsby*. He sometimes uses words that do not usually go together to make a feeling. He also uses symbols to make feelings. Fitzgerald uses colors as symbols. He uses gold, green, white, gray, and red, pink. In *The Great Gatsby*, Fitzgerald gives colors special meanings. He uses these meanings later to make people remember feelings about things.

Fitzgerald gives white and gray the meaning of being the same. White is better and more fancy. Gray is old and not as good. Fitzgerald shows this at the start of the book. People wear white a lot. Daisy and Jordan wear “white” (8). Everyone wears white: Nick wears “white flannels” (41) to Gatsby’s party. Tom wears a “white shirt” (36) when he meets Myrtle. Catherine is “powdered milky white” (30). The only time people do not wear white is when Nick sees Gatsby’s party. Nick says the party is “gaudy with primary colors” (40). Fitzgerald uses white and gray to describe normal things too. Nick goes to work “down the white chasms of lower New York” (56). The names at Gatsby’s party are “gray names” (61). Catherine’s apartment is “one slice in a long white cake of apartment-houses” (28). Fitzgerald describes common people and places as white or gray too. Jordan and Daisy had a “white girlhood” (19). There are “gray cars” and “gray land” (23) in the valley of ashes. The “Italian child” on the train is “gray” (26). The dog-seller is “a gray old man” (27).

After Fitzgerald uses white and gray a lot, he uses them to show unimportant things. He does this with Daisy. After a long time without using these colors, Fitzgerald says Daisy is “dressed in white” in “a little white roadster” (74). People start to see Daisy as less of a person and more like something that Gatsby wants. Fitzgerald uses white and gray more to show Daisy this way. Daisy’s fur collar is “a gray haze” (18). She wears “white” (115) before Tom and Gatsby talk.

San Diego County is good for farming. The weather is warm and sunny. Farmers grow many things: tomatoes, oranges, lettuce, squash, broccoli, herbs, peaches, lemons, berries, honey, and peppers. Many people in San Diego want to buy food from farms that do not use chemicals. There are many small farms in the area. They have long waiting lists for their food. People like to buy organic eggs and milk. Many farms also let people visit. They can walk, look for birds, and learn about farming.

Farming without chemicals is good for plants and animals. It helps them to live better. But, it can be more hard work. Farmers must work hard to keep pests and weeds away. They must also use more time to take care of the soil. Farms that do not use chemicals are often smaller.

The land is near a town called Potrero. It is 160 acres of bushes, grass, and trees. It is next to a big forest. Many animals live there. Some are in danger of disappearing. 

People have lived here for a long time. First, Native Americans lived there. Then, ranchers came. They raised cattle and sold wood. This land was used for many years for farming.

I looked at a website to find land for sale. I found land near Potrero. I looked at programs to help farmers. I wanted to know how farmers can make money and help the animals. I found a farm near Potrero that does not use chemicals.

Culture is very important in talks. Culture is what people do and think. Culture is not the same for every person. It is not one thing. Saying all people from one place are the same is wrong. It is better to know how a culture thinks about a topic. This can help in talks.

When you meet people from another culture, you see it like your own culture. You may compare the two.

To understand another culture, study its history. Look at its good and bad parts. Do not judge a culture or try to change it. Accept it as it is. Work with it. This is very important in talks. If you are not strong in a talk, you need to respect the other culture more.

Culture is not just about countries. Companies have their own cultures too. Some companies work long hours. Others work less. You can see a company's culture in how people dress, how they talk, and how they hire people. Some companies like to help people. Others do not. Look at how different companies in America are. You can see how many different ways there are to think in one country.

Some cultures are not as different as American culture. They may look the same on the outside. But there are still many differences.

Values are important to understand. Values are why people do things. If people value saving face or being kind, they will not be mean in a talk. If people value hard work, they will not give up easily.

Learn about the other side before a talk. This can help you talk better.

The fool say, "There is no God." This is from the Bible. This is also what St. Anselm think about when he talk about God. St. Thomas Aquinas also think this way. Both men try to prove that God is real. We will look at their ideas to see which one is better. 

We must start by saying that both men believe in the God of the Bible. We cannot use a different God.

Both men make good points. But neither one give us a perfect reason to believe in God. 

First, we look at St. Anselm. Anselm say we find God by looking inside our minds. He say that because we can think about God, God must exist. This idea can be hard to understand. It is like faith. Faith is believing in something even if you can not prove it. Anselm say we do not need proof from the world around us. 

St. Thomas Aquinas think different. He say we can prove God exists using logic and what we see in the world. This is good for telling people about God because they can use reason to believe. Aquinas give five reasons why God must exist. He say that things change, things need a cause, things are not always perfect, some things are better than others, and the world is in harmony.

Long ago, a prince was born. This prince one day became Buddha. Buddha left the world and became wise. His ideas made Buddhism. Buddhism is very old. It is more than two thousand years old. Buddhism looks different now than when Buddha lived. 

For example, in Sri Lanka, there is a water ceremony each year. Monks and people do this ceremony. It is important to them, even though Buddha did not teach about it. Buddhism has changed a lot. 

We will talk about why. We will use some words. An "internal force" is from Buddhists. A "hostile force" wants to hurt Buddhism. A "benign force" does not try to hurt or help Buddhism.

First, we will talk about the ideas of Buddhism. Buddhists believe in three things: Buddha, Dhamma, and Sangha. Dhamma is Buddhist teaching. It is in three parts: Sutras, rules for monks, and ideas about how things work. 

Buddhists say life is full of suffering.  They say we can end suffering if we stop wanting things.

The United States and Mexico had a big problem for many years. This problem lasted fifty-seven years, from 1836 to 1893.  The two countries fought a war in 1846 and 1848. The United States won the war. The United States took Texas and land in the southwest.  

Many other problems happened between the two countries.  The problems stopped before World War One. The problems began because Americans and Mexicans had different ideas about religion, culture, and how to live. They also had different ideas about money and land.

Many countries that are close together have problems. They share land and want the same things. The United States and Mexico are not the only countries with problems.

David M. Pletcher said that only Mexico and Cuba have always had problems with the United States. These countries are near the United States.


Religion was also a problem between the United States and Mexico.  Many countries have had problems because of religion. Sally Frahm said that Americans were against Catholicism and kings in the 1700s and 1800s.  This is like the Cold War, when the United States and the Soviet Union did not like each other.

The United States and Mexico did not trust each other because of problems between England and Spain. These countries were in charge of Mexico and the United States in the past.


Diehl and Goerts said that Mexico and the United States had seventeen problems in fifty-seven years. Most of the problems were about land. Bandits from the United States caused problems in Mexico. Both countries used soldiers to stop the bandits.


Schmitt said that Mexico became dependent on the United States. This helped to stop the problems.  By the 1800s, the United States wanted to help Mexico economically instead of taking more land.

Fifteen years ago I became sick. I did not know I was sick. I was a nurse. I chose this job. I wanted to help people. When I was young, people said, "You will always have a job. People get sick." So I became a nurse.

I was 46. I was single. I had no money. I could not work. I am still sick. I live on government help. I have nothing. Every day is hard. I am not safe. I do not feel good about myself. I do not know what will happen next. But I know this: I could not live without my family and friends.

Life has many problems. Big problems and small problems. We cannot always be ready for everything. We need to help each other.

Some people say we need to be strong and take care of ourselves. But our country was built by people who helped each other. They shared food and tools. They cared for each other.

I am prepared for problems. I have supplies for emergencies. But I also know it is good to be kind to my neighbors.

Why do living things change over time? Are there limits to these changes?

A long time ago, a scientist named D’Arcy Thompson said that we do not yet know how to describe life in math. This is still true today.

Now, we are using math to study how shells change shape.

We looked at the shells of a type of snail called Prunum. We used math to make pictures of what the shells could look like. Then we looked at real shells to see how they compare.

A shell is like a tube that turns in a circle. Each turn is called a whorl. The whorls are on a line called the columella.

The whorls can grow at different speeds. 

We can see how the whorls are connected by lines called sutures. The biggest whorl is the last one. 

The small part at the top is called the apex. The opposite end is the base. The animal comes out of its shell through an opening called the aperture.


We can look at a shell from many different angles. 

We can count the whorls by looking at the shell from the top.

We can think of a shell as a series of openings that grow over time.  We can use math to track the growth of the openings.

Indonesia has a problem with baby and child death.  The death rate has not changed much in ten years. Indonesia is making progress on some goals, like clean water. But the health of babies and mothers needs to get better. 

Indonesia has more births with a helper. But some helpers are not doctors.  They can not help if a birth is difficult. This makes many mothers die.

Fewer children get help for sickness now.  We do not know much about help after a baby is born, but it is a problem.

Some babies are born with a cut in their belly. This is done in hospitals.  But it happens less in the countryside. This means rich people get better help.

Poor people have big problems getting help. They have to pay a lot of money.

What can Indonesia do to help?  They can make new programs to fix the problems. But new programs can be bad.

New programs can cost a lot of money and make other problems.  It is better to make the whole health system stronger.

Victorian books are known for much detail. They often talk about rich people from that time. Two books from this time that are different are Oliver Twist and Wuthering Heights. These books have mystery and strange things in them. This is not normal for books from that time. This makes the people in the book more interesting. We learn more about why they act the way they do and how they feel.

“Many new and confusing ideas came to his mind. He seemed to be walking between Sikes and Crackit. They were angry and arguing. He could hear their words. Then he saw himself talking to them. Suddenly, he heard gunshots. He saw lights and heard shouts. Someone was taking him away quickly. He was in pain, and it would not go away.” 
(Dickens, 220)

These books use mystery often in dreams. But the dreams are different in each book. In Oliver Twist, the strange dreams show us what is inside Oliver. We see his pain and how he sees the world. When Oliver is shot, he remembers it in a dream. He is trying to find help. The part shows that Oliver had no control. He was very sick. He saw Sikes and Crackit, which shows he was in a lot of pain. The shooting was too much for him. His senses were gone. He did not see the hand that took him away. He was sad and scared.

Whose fault was it that Oliver was hurt? It was not his fault. He could not stop what happened. This shows that Oliver has no control. He could not even try to stop it, even when his life was in danger. The story shows that Oliver is losing hope. Fagin is hurting him. He is making Oliver feel hopeless. He can’t fight back.

“The day went by. It was gone quickly. Night came. Night was long and quiet. It was also short because it went by quickly.”

A few years ago, I work in a after school program. I help young students. I was good at English and reading. A teacher ask me to help a boy named Adrian. He was in third or fourth grade. He have trouble reading.

Something was wrong. He read some letters good, but other letters, he no read good. Adrian speak perfect English. We try to help him. His mother come to the school. She no speak English. She speak Spanish. I know a little Spanish. We talk a little. Then I understand. Adrian know how to read, but he no know the English letters well.

I tell this story about Adrian to talk about the problem of language in schools. It is not always easy to see the problem. Even if a child speak English well, reading can be hard. We all know this is a problem. What can we do?

Adrian need help with English reading and letters. For children who do not speak much English, the problem is harder. There is no one way to fix this. We need to use many ideas. 

One idea is to teach in two languages. This is good for all children. It help children learn. Some people are afraid of this. They are afraid it waste money. But it is not true. If we teach in two languages, all children will learn more.

How can we do this? All teachers cannot speak two languages. That is not possible. But we can have teachers who speak two languages. They can help the children.

We are small.  We learn this when we are young. Some go to church to learn about the big things. Others go to temple. Some look inside. Many people take the religion of their family. Some people do not agree. They say there is nothing beyond our lives. We can change our beliefs. We all look for good things in the world. We want to see the light.

My father liked cardinals. I asked him one day. We sat on the porch. It rained. We smoked. Water ran down the sides of the house. It was hard to see. My father looked far away. He was thin. His hair was not as thick. He did not look at me. I felt alone. I was afraid. I did not talk.

My father died in December. He was sick for a long time. The doctors said he would not live long. But he lived a little longer. I did not know why. I did not pray. I did not think God was listening.

I did not watch him die. I could not. I did not want to see him go. I wanted to remember him as he was. I knew him better than anyone else. He would not want me to watch. I stayed in bed for days. No one called.

The "Gothic Novel" is old and new. It is like a puzzle.  Some say it is bad. Others say it is good. Some say it is not deep. Others say it is very good.  The first Gothic Novel was "The Castle of Otranto." The writer was Horace Walpole. He used old stories and new stories. He made a new kind of story. He called it "A Gothic Story."

Gothic stories have old things from the past. They have old buildings, stories, and ideas.  People used the word "gothic" a long time ago. It meant old or not good.  But the Gothic Novel is new. It is a new way to tell stories.

One idea in Gothic stories is chivalry. Chivalry is about knights. Knights were brave and good. Gothic writers liked chivalry. They did not see it in people today.

In "The Castle of Otranto," there is a knight named Frederic. He is brave and good. He is like a knight from the old stories. 

Walpole wrote this story a long time ago. He was worried about the future. He thought people were not as good as they used to be. Frederic is an example of this idea.

Supply chain management is the way goods move. Goods go from a customer order to the factory. They go from raw materials to the customer.  The term supply chain management was new in 1982. A man named Keith Oliver made up the term. Keith Oliver said that supply chain management is how a company plans, does, and checks the things that happen in the supply chain. It helps companies give customers what they want quickly and well.

There are six things that make up a supply chain:

1. Making things
2. Getting materials
3. Storing things
4. Where things are made
5. Moving things around
6. Sharing information

Managers use these six things to help customers.

Making things is the first step. Making things is the start of the whole process.

Managers need to know what customers want. They can look at the market to know what people want. The market tells managers what customers need. 

When managers know what customers want, they can decide what things to make. They can also decide how many things to make.

After that, managers decide where to make things. They choose a place that is good for making a lot of things and making things that are good. 

The next step is to plan how much work each worker will do. Managers must also take care of the machines. 

Making things is very important. Every small part is important. If managers do not plan carefully, the company will waste time and money.

The second thing in supply chain management is getting things. Getting things is the way a company decides how to make things and how to work with other companies.

A company may have many different places to make things. Each place has different workers, machines, and skills. Managers must choose which place to use for each part of the product. 

Managers may also give some work to other companies. 

This is called outsourcing. 

Companies do this to make things faster and cheaper.

Hitler live in Burma, sign say. Ellen Page, star of Juno, stand alone on street corner. She hold a piece of cardboard. The sign have a message. It say, "Hitler live in Burma." Burma is a country in Southeast Asia. It have a strong government. In 2007, people protest in Burma. Monks lead the protest. It call "The Saffron Revolution." The monks wear yellow robes.

At first, the government let the monks protest. But then, the protest get bad. The government use force against the monks. Soldiers attack the monks. Journalists get hurt. One journalist, Kenji Nagai, die. Many people die in the protest.

This is not new. Governments try to stop people from speaking out.  

Roman emperors say they are gods. They rule over people. Japanese emperors are also gods. They rule Japan. Our president, George W. Bush, talk to Ted Haggard. Haggard lead a group called "Stupid People Worldwide."

People protest in many places. In 1989, people protest in Tiananmen Square. The Chinese government use force. Many people die. In Rwanda, people kill many Tutsis. Hitler start a war against Jewish people.

Duke Ellington good at jazz music. He play long time and make good music. Ellington play piano, but he good at make music for other players too. He make music where players can sing and play own music. Ellington music have many parts that fit together. It sound good together. 

One book about music say Ellington use voice like instrument. He use voice in song called "Creole Love Call." Voice sound like music, not like words. Ellington music help players show their own style. This song have many parts. 

First part: Voice and music play back and forth. Voice start soft, then get rough.
Second part: Trumpet play soft, make music longer.
Third part: Clarinet play high, piano play soft.

She always felt she need some thing.  She want some thing but she did not know what. This feeling start when she was about 14 years old.  She is now 17. She want a person, not a thing. She did not like any boys. Some boy want to be friend with her. They try to talk to her but she did not like them. She ask her self why this happen. She think about it for many years. She have many idea but she not know the answer. She live her life and ask her self about this feeling.

Her home was a calm place. Her parent are good and calm. They never argue. They very seldom argue with her. They only argue when she want to do her own thing. She is the daughter of calm parent but she is a fun person. 

Today was not a calm day. She walk from room to room. She want to find something new. She hear a short scream. It was her mother's voice. She run to the kitchen. She was scared. She ask "Mom! Mom! What is wrong?" Her mother was on the floor. She look hurt. Her mother say "Ow". Her daughter run to her and put her hand on her mother. "Ouch...sweet...I need you to take me to the hospital." Her mother say this word fast. Her daughter know she is in pain. "Okay mom. Where can I get you?" Her mother point.  Her daughter was happy she take class to make her strong. She pick up her mother and put her in the car. She drive to the hospital.

The hospital smell like medicine and sickness. She was not scared. She was thinking about her mother. She run to the doctor with her mother. The doctor look at her mother. They take her to a room. Her daughter had to wait.

Her mother fell from a tall step stool. She try to get a vase from a high shelf.

This study looked at the effect of a special diet, called the “Mediterranean Diet” (Med diet). The study found that women who ate more like this diet had less risk of heart disease and stroke.

The Med diet has lots of plants, like fruits, nuts, and beans. It also has healthy fats and fish. It has less meat and fat from animals. People can also drink a little wine with this diet.

Scientists before had looked at the Med diet and saw that it helped people live longer. This new study looked at heart disease and stroke.

The study followed 74,886 women between the ages of 38 and 63. They did not have heart disease or diabetes. The women answered questions about what they ate for many years.

The study found that women who ate more like the Med diet had less chance of getting heart disease or stroke. This study shows that the Med diet is good for people's health.

In two thousand seven, the United States had a big money problem. People lost jobs. Houses cost less money. Many big companies had problems. This problem is still here. We must ask: why did this happen? How can we stop it? 

The problem was bad choices in politics. Banks gave away money to people who could not pay it back. This made the money system weak. Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac took these bad loans and sold them to other people. When people could not pay, the banks had no money. This made the whole money system very sick.

This problem started in the year nineteen ninety-nine. President Clinton wanted to be president again. He wanted people to like him. So, he made it easy for people to get loans. This made the problem worse later. A writer for the New York Times said this would be bad. He said it would be like the money problem in the 1980s.

There were many reasons for the problem. New kinds of loans made things more complicated. People took out big loans they could not pay back. This made the money system very risky.

The housing market fell. Banks had lost a lot of money. Big companies had to sell for very little. Some companies closed. Fannie and Freddie needed help from the government.

Exposition.  This is the part in a story where you show what you can do as a writer. You make the reader happy. Or, maybe you make them sleepy.  Dr. Merlin gets mad when people write too much exposition. It is not good.

People know the rule: "Show, don't tell." But Dr. Merlin still sees writers write long parts with nothing happening. Exposition is bad.

Exposition tells the reader what happened. It is like a character in a movie saying a lot of words all at once.  In a book, the writer tells the reader.

Here is an example. The story says a woman met her husband at a place and time. They got married. Then her husband died. 

The reader does not want to read two pages about this. The reader wants to see the husband. See how he talks. See how he acts.  The reader wants to see how the woman feels about him.  This helps the reader care about what happens.

The writer should show the husband's good heart. Show how much he loves the woman. This helps the reader care about him.  Then, when he dies, the reader will be sad. 

Writers need to give the reader more than just the basic story. They need to give the reader details.

It is easy to rush past details. Maybe a new character was in the Air Force. Now he works at a gas station. He is divorced.  He likes to fish.  He wants to own the gas station someday.

I see two news reports from Columbus, Ohio. The first report was from NBC 4. It was live this morning (August 13, 2011). The main story was about a man in Ashley, Ohio. He hurt his wife. The news did not say her name, but his name was Shad Hostettler. They showed his picture. He looked bad. They talked about this story for two minutes. They said he hurt his wife many times. He was caught. I think they talked about this story for enough time.

The second story was about a man named Travis Buyers. He was 18 years old. He was hurt by a gun in Sharon Woods. He was very hurt. No one was caught. The police were looking for the person who did it. This story was short. I think this was because the man was Black. I see this often. The news does not talk much about Black people when they are hurt. If a white person is hurt, the news talks a lot about it. 

The next story was about a hole in a helicopter. Police think someone shot the helicopter with a small gun. Crime-Stoppers will pay five thousand dollars to find the person who shot the helicopter. 

The next story was about rain. They said it would rain on Saturday. It would be hot this weekend. The story was short. They wanted people to watch more news.

They also talked about a robbery. A man robbed a store in Columbus. He was Black and wore a hood. He was tall and thin. I think they talked too much about the man’s race. 

The last story was about a man named Rene Rodriguez. He was from Texas. He was in jail for selling drugs. He will be in jail for a long time. The news said 300 months. I do not know why they said that. They also said he was Hispanic. I do not think that was important to the story.

Brothers have a strong link. This link can bring many feelings: love, pride, envy, and meanness. Brothers know each other very well. They see themselves in each other. When things are hard, the true bond shows. It can be good or bad. These feelings can have a big cost. To understand these feelings, we must look at the results. When a brother looks in another's eyes, he sees his own face. He sees himself as he really is, not how others see him. A brother's actions show his true character.

In the story "The Scarlet Ibis", two brothers show this link. They go on a hard journey in a beautiful place. There is sadness and pride at the end. Only one brother lives.

We learn about the brothers through how they act and talk. We also see the world through the main character's eyes. His feelings and how he sees the world change how he acts.

The main character feels pride. He wants a brother to learn from, like running and climbing. He wants a brother to play with. But Doodle, his brother, is sick. He cannot run or play. It makes the main character sad. He is even angry. He thinks about hurting Doodle. But then Doodle smiles, and the main character feels love. He wants to help Doodle.

The human brain is a complex thing. It helps us think and create. As time goes on, we learn new things about the brain. We use words to talk about it. First, we said it was like a wax tablet. Then, we said it was like paper. Now, we say it is like a computer. But remember, these words are just ways to talk about it. They do not show us everything.

We get information from our senses. Our eyes, ears, skin, smell, and taste tell us about the world. Our brain changes this information. It looks for patterns. For example, if we see a box, our brain sees the color, shape, and edges. This helps us know what it is. Our brain also uses what we already know. If we see a black box, we know it is a box, not a hole.

Our brain chooses what is important. It pays attention to some things and not others. We see many things, but our brain only notices what is important. For example, we might hear many sounds, but we hear our name clearly.

Our brain stores information. There are different kinds of memory. We have short-term memory and long-term memory. We remember things for a short time, and then we may remember them for a long time.

We do not know exactly how our brain works. Some people think it is like a network. Ideas are connected to each other. For example, the idea of "chair" is connected to the idea of "table".

Aldous Huxley look at the danger of new technology and the business system. He write a story called Brave New World. In this story, people value being part of a group more than being alone. They want to be happy, always. The people are like pieces in a big game. They live in a world with only one way to think, set by a leader called the World Controller. If we look at the story with Marxist ideas, we see that Huxley is worried about these systems.

Words like "same" and "things" show that Huxley thinks the story is a warning about problems with the economy.

Huxley show how business is bad using a Marxist idea called "false thinking." The regular people do not know the real way business works. They only think about making money. This is because the leaders control what they think. The workers in Brave New World are taught to buy things and spend money. This is controlled by the World Controller.

Huxley also show how some groups have more power than others. The poor people do not know they are being controlled. The rich people know but do not care. Only a few rich people, like Bernard, try to change things.

In Brave New World, people do not have real relationships. They are not deep or interesting. Maybe Huxley is saying that technology and business take away people's freedom.

There is no love or strong feelings in the story. People talk in a simple way about each other. They care only about looks. The people in each group are happy with their place in society. This shows how business can control people.

I study at University Park. I have been a student for two and a half years. Many students have a hard time getting around. My first year, I lived in an East Halls dorm. It was far from most of the buildings. It took up to 25 minutes to walk to classes. I talked to a graduate. He said long ago, there was a lot of empty space. Now, there are new buildings. There are also sports fields and apartments. The campus is getting bigger. It is harder to get around.

What is the best way to move around campus? Bicycles are good. But the campus needs to be good for bikes. I know a friend who rode a bike again. He said, “Bikes are great! It is the best way to move around.” Bicycles are good for you. They are also fast. You can go far on a little food. I live off campus now. It is far from the center of campus. I bought a bike. It is a good decision. I can get to class in five minutes!

The road to my class is not always good. But, I need to get to class. If I did not have a bike, I would have to walk. It would take a lot of time. I am too busy to walk.

In pursuing an education in social work, I intend to follow a career path with the Division of Family and Children Services to help children who have been abused or neglected; and to provide support for troubled families. Values that I can provide to the social work field include the following: service, respect, ethical nature, commitment to help improve relationships between others and to improve myself professionally to remain competent in my field. These core values are not just important to social workers; they are important to me personally. 

	I have always wanted to help others, but I was unsure of the career path that I wanted to follow. Throughout my years in high school and college, I saw many individuals flee from their problems in denial and a few used coping mechanisms that were less than ideal. Because of situations that I have witnessed, I chose to pursue a Bachelor’s degree in Psychology. Still unsure of a career path, I decided to take a break once I graduated from Piedmont College in 2009. One day that summer, I visited a friend who introduced me to a sixteen year-old boy sitting nervously on her couch. She explained to me why he was visiting: to escape his abusive parents. The next day, I learned that he had called the police to his parent’s residence. To see if I could help in any way, I drove over to his parents’ house. Once there, I privately explained my concerns to the police and told them I had just graduated with a degree in Psychology from Piedmont College. The police requested that I talk to the parents since there was nothing that the law could do for the teenager. When I questioned the parents about the situation, they seemed nervous and used excuses to describe their son’s “manipulative” behavior for involving outside sources to resolve “simple” disputes. After this particular experience, I began to seriously consider a career in social work to help children with “simple” disputes among family members.

	Another value that is important for the field of social work is social justice. As a society, we claim that the individual is important and we mourn those that we have lost. The concept of the “individual” that society holds is more a follower of archaic traditions than actual uniqueness. So, if society mourns lost individuals, then why do we strive to be similar to “everyone else?” I am an individual and do not enjoy placing limitations on myself to be similar to others. Throughout my years at high school and college, I protested against social injustice whenever I could: coloring my hair unnatural colors, wearing clothing that fit my personality, piercing my ears past the traditional set, declaring my involvement with GSBA (Gay Straight Bisexual Alliance), fighting against both racism and discrimination whenever I witnessed it, etc. I believe in social justice and I will continue to protest against social injustice.

The following paper addresses the Biological and Sociocultural models in relation to the disorder insomnia. The biological model focuses on genetic information that is inherited as well as medical aspects of health. The Sociocultural models look at environmental relationships and their applications to race, ethnicity, demographics, and socioeconomic status. The following review of insomnia looks at these models and explains each piece of research chosen to relate to and to better explain the models. The explanations of the research and their findings are then critiqued to mention their specific strengths and weaknesses.

A sleep disorder can be characterized as a primary sleep disorder, a sleep disorder related to another mental disorder, or a sleep disorder related to other issues. The Primary sleep disorders are Dyssonmias or Parasomnias while sleep disorders related to another mental disorder are related to an Axis I or Axis II disorder. Other categories of sleep disorders can be due to medical complications or the intake of a substance. The Dyssomnias are: Primary Insomnia, Primary Hypersomnia, Narcolepsy, Breathing- Related Sleep Disorder, Circadian Rhythm Sleep Disorder, and Dyssomnia Not Otherwise Specified (NOS). While Primary Insomnia is a complication in adequate or maintained sleep, Primary Hypersomnia is a difficulty in staying awake, both for at least a one month period of time. Narcolepsy involves cataplexy and/ or automatic REM. While Dyssonmias focus on initiating and remaining asleep, the Parasomnias are sleep disorders associated with behavioral abnormalities and/ or physiological occurrences. Parasomnias are Nightmare Disorder, Sleep Terror Disorder, Sleepwalking Disorder, and Parasomnias Not Otherwise Specified. The sleep disorders related to another mental disorder involve sleep difficulties due to Axis I (Clinical Disorders) or Axis II (Personality Disorders or Mental Retardation). The following review focuses on insomnia, and somewhat on primary sleep disorders in general in relation to the biological and sociocultural models.

	 The biological model of sleep disorders focuses on genes, heritable factors, and physiologically acquired aspect of sleep disorders. Neurons in the hypothalamus containing orexin are responsible for the regulation of sleep and wakefulness. This study experimented with mice and found that there are phenotypic GABAB receptors on the orexin neurons which are specifically responsible for sleep/ wake states. The activation of the GABAA receptor induces responses that promote sleep. If it is inhibited from firing, this can cause reduced anxiety and induce sleep. The GABAB agonist (baclofen) increased sleep time (Matsuki et al., 2009). Such results imply that the animal models of mice can be generalized to studies in humans. This shows that there is a genetic and environmental basis for the physical GABAB receptor in humans. A problem or absence with this receptor could alter the ability of one to have adequate sleep without medication. The sociocultural implication of this study is that if the phenotype was inherited, this could regulate sleep, and an alteration of the receptor would naturally disturb sleep for an individual. This would negatively impact aspects of life such as school, career, and every day events that involve monotonous tasks and focus.

This paper covers three areas of Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD). First, a brief definition of the disorder is provided. Next, diagnosis is explained, with common characteristics, or “red flags”. Finally, the paper concludes with ways that a teacher in a mainstreamed classroom environment can assist a student with CAPD.

	Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD), or Auditory Processing Disorder (APD) “refers to the efficiency and effectiveness by which the central nervous system (CNS) utilizes auditory information. Narrowly defined, (C)AP refers to the perceptual processing of auditory information in the CNS and the neurobiologic activity that underlies that processing and gives rise to electrophysiologic auditory potentials” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005), meaning it is a disorder wherein the central nervous system (i.e. the brain) cannot properly process things that are heard. People with CAPD can hear normally, and are therefore not considered “hearing impaired”; rather, the area of the brain that translates what we hear, separating words or differentiating conversation from background noise does not function as it typically should. 

	The earliest mention of the disorder that became CAPD is from the mid-1950s, called “auditory imperception” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005) when researchers were evaluating children with communicative disorders. The Italian research team of Bocca, Calearo, and Cassinari began developing tests for these children in 1954; in 1961, Kimura “introduced dichotic testing and formulated a model to explain the physiology of the CANS underlying dichotic perception” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005). A national conference was held in 1977 that stimulated research on children with CAPD. 

	CAPD manifests itself in multiple ways: the person suffering may not be able to localize or hear sound in space; may have difficulty discriminating between two or more “acoustic events” (sound occurrences); may not be able to recognize sound patterns; may not be able to differentiate changes in speech (like detecting sarcasm based on change of voice); one sound may be blocked by a subsequent sound; may not have the ability to synthesize sound clues (that is, interpret in a meaningful way that they can then act upon); and may not be able to determine the sequence in which auditory information is presented (Ferre).

	In order to diagnose CAPD, the patient must be screened with “systematic observation of listening behavior and/or performance on tests of auditory function”, which may be conducted by “audiologists, SLPs, psychologists, and others using a variety of measures that evaluate auditory-related skills” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005). This may include questionnaires and surveys, observation of auditory behaviors, including how the patient responds to certain stimuli. There is, at this time, no one tool or test that is used consistently to a high rate of diagnostic success, and there is no known cause for the disorder. Many tests used present the patient with multiple, simultaneous auditory stimuli and then ask for them to differentiate certain items, like a series of words or numbers. More advanced tests include recording acoustic signals within the ear and measuring the responses to the signals.

The play Twelfth Night seems to say that although disguise is in fact useful in perpetrating long bouts of deception, in the end a person must reject that newly formed guise, or else risk losing themselves forever in the process. A big problem with ending a deception, however, is that one may find themselves alienated in the process. Therefore, in the end, one must decide between one’s own self preservation, or the preservation of relationships with those around them. For although some will respond neutrally to discovering that they’ve been tricked, still others will not take the deception so lightly, and will be likely be offended by the whole charade.
The topic of deception in gender role reversal is especially problematic, because it brings up many side issues, perhaps the most important one being, why? Why does the subject feel the need to shirk their own identity and take up a disguise in the form of the opposite gender? In Viola’s case, it is obviously a form of self protection.: “I’ll bring you to a captain in this town/ Where lie my maiden weeds, by whose gentle help/ I was preserved to serve this noble count…” (5.1.247-249)
Having newly arrived in a foreign land, Viola feels it necessary to pretend to be a man to protect herself from would be attackers. Viola’s plan works, but it also alienates her from the women around her, cutting her off from an important support system. To make matters worse, she is apparently so convincing at appearing to be a man that Olivia confuses her with Sebastian, and in effect falls in love with her. “Whither, my lord? Cesario, husband, stay.” (5.1.138) On top of that, she also has to deal with suppressed romantic desires between her and Orsino: “Boy, thou hast said to me a thousand times/ Thou never shouldst love woman like to me.” (5.1. 260-261)
Although this may be a somewhat progressive attitude, to the modern reader, Twelfth Night may be seen as an illustration of how deception may help facilitate the unveiling of suppressed emotions, especially in the cases of Olivia and Orsino. Certain passages seem to hint that the aforesaid characters may have unexpressed subconscious desires that the appearance of Viola/Cesario forces them to deal with. For instance, is Olivia attracted to Cesario because Cesario appears to be a man, or does Olivia really secretly harbor feelings for women? One would argue that this is probably not the case, because Shakespeare’s character Olivia seems more likely to be parodying those people of his time period who judge others only upon their looks. 
This is evidenced by the ease with which Olivia switches her romantic ardors from Cesario to Sebastian, and begins to regard Cesario/Viola as family rather than a love interest: “A sister, you are she.” (5.1.315)

German colonial rule has been noted by various observers for its brutality, notably with respect to the genocide of the Ovaherero and Nama in German South West Africa. Of course nothing so broad as an entire colonial empire can be accounted for by such a simple description. The German colonial empire was as varied in policies and ruling style as it was in geography. Educational provision across the colonies was similarly diverse. When the British took over German East Africa (Tanganyika) in 1919, they found a large population of educated and literate Africans. German educational efforts in Kamerun and other colonies were also praised by contemporary authors. 
The situation in South West Africa (present-day Namibia) presented a stark contrast.  Unlike in East Africa, where the government established state schools and played a prominent role in the education of the natives, in South West Africa the task of native education was left almost entirely to missionary societies that received limited government support. The government did however invest significant resources towards the education of Europeans in the colony, establishing s system of state schools as well as more heavily supporting and regulating missionary schools. These educational policies had longstanding effects on South West Africa, even after German rule. While other German colonies boasted significant numbers of literate and educated Africans, in South West Africa “the overwhelming majority of the population remained untouched, uneducated, and illiterate.” Various social, political, and economic factors led to the divergent experience of South West Africa. This paper seeks to expand the discussion by identifying these factors and paying particular attention to new research on the attitudes of settlers and colonial authorities to native Africans.
There is a wealth of literature dealing with education in the German colonial empire specifically. Most of these sources are in German and were written in the early twentieth century, during or shortly after the period of German colonial rule. The aim of early works was primarily to describe the features of educational systems in these colonies. Later writings in English expanded the discourse through comparative studies of education in the various German colonies and more detailed analyses of specific aspects of education. These studies illustrated significant differences in the educational systems of different colonies. The most prominent work to explicitly address the topic of this paper is Cohen’s study of education in South West Africa and East Africa. Cohen compares the educational systems of the two colonies and discusses the factors that account for the differences between them. According to Cohen, the large settler population of South West Africa explains many of the distinguishing aspects of the colony’s educational system.
Compared to Germany’s other colonial possessions, South West Africa had a moderately temperate climate, although much of the territory is covered by arid desert. The European population of South West Africa reflected the relatively hospitable conditions. By 1913 nearly 15,000 whites lived in South West Africa, while only 5,336 lived in the colony with the next largest settler population, East Africa.

‎	‏The classification of Popular Music has grown over the past‭ ‬100‭ ‬years to include so many genres that it is difficult to definitively list them all. Complicating matters,‭ ‬most if not all genres—rap,‭ ‬rock,‭ ‬country,‭ ‬jazz,‭ ‬folk,‭ ‬just to name a few—have spawned multiple sub and sub-sub genres within their domain.  Arguably the sub-genre of Heavy Metal rock has become one of the most diverse and expressive genres of all popular music in the past‭ ‬40‭ ‬years. It is expressive because it displays a wide range of emotions,‭ ‬although they tend to lean toward the darker side of the spectrum. It is diverse in that quite soon after the beginnings of the genre,‭ ‬people started to realize that it had real flexibility and started to take advantage of it to create their own sub-genre,‭ ‬which then was followed by sub-sub-genres,‭ ‬and the chain continues until today. 

Today we have reached a point in the heavy metal movement where there are so many niches of groups that it is hard to determine what exactly heavy metal is. It has grown to incorporate so many themes from other genres,‭ ‬but like everything else,‭ ‬it spawned from somewhere. In order to properly understand the metal music that exists everywhere today,‭ ‬one must first understand what the metal movement is,‭ ‬and why it’s a movement rather than just a genre.

‎	‏Metal is,‭ ‬in many ways,‭ ‬a movement defined by darkness. Metal can be considered a‭ “‬music of more‭”—‬more bass,‭ ‬more volume,‭ ‬more violence,‭ ‬more theatricality. Less primitivism,‭ ‬more chops‭; ‬people in metal bands really know how to play their instrument,‭ ‬and it comes through in the music. Metal is also—although it may not come as a surprise—a movement that is heavily drug induced. There was a psychedelic drug boom in the mid-70‭’‬s that led to people getting crazier,‭ ‬leading to them to make crazy,‭ ‬other-worldly records,‭ ‬using the drugs as a scapegoat for their creation. It possesses many dark,‭ ‬visceral qualities,‭ ‬which was very new to the music scene because a large amount of popular music had qualities that weren’t true to the darker side of the emotional spectrum. Also,‭ ‬later generations of metal have taken some of their influence from the dark,‭ ‬visceral qualities that were so present in the Romantic Era. Lyrics such as the following express the darkness that is such a staple of the movement:‭ (‬Byrne‭)‬


	
These lyrics from Helter Skelter display the darker side of the Beatles. It exhibits an up and down,‭ ‬supposedly that of drugs. This song is considered by some to be one of the first Heavy Metal songs. It was a response to a Rolling Stones song that was also on the heavier,‭ ‬darker side. The Beatles wanted to prove that they could be just as heavy as the Stones,‭ ‬so they put that song on‭ ‬The White Album.

A few decades before the Surrealist artists began painting their dreamlike works, the artist Henri Rousseau was carefully crafting his own dreams, literally and figuratively. The Dream, a 1910 painting by the famous Post-Impressionist artist, represents not only a woman in awe at the wonders of the land she visits within a dream, but also Rousseau’s own personal dreams and goals as a painter. Since beginning his work, he dreamed of recognition, acceptance, and praise by other artists and art lovers, and found that he was faced with a difficult internal dilemma to achieve this aspiration. The Dream is Henri Rousseau’s work that best reflects his career-long internal struggle: to either conform to or mimic certain styles of painting in order to be accepted by the critical art world he so adored, or to allow himself to be creatively independent and unique, leaving his own path as he went.
Before one can analyze The Dream through this perspective, one must first be somewhat familiar with Rousseau’s biographical story. Henri Rousseau was born on May 21, 1844, in the town of Laval in northwest France. His father was a tinsmith and hardware dealer who “enjoyed bourgeois prosperity” (Shattuck 47). Growing up, he received no formal training in the arts; instead, he was employed until the age of forty working for France as a gabelou, or employee of the municipal toll service, although he received the misnomer sobriquet of douanier, a customs inspector (Shattuck 46). The death of his first wife, Clémence, which followed the deaths of eight infant children, left Rousseau with only one child, a daughter named Julia, and immense grief (Shattuck 49). He therefore hoped to take refuge in a new life and pursued painting to offer him comfort and fresh beginnings. Unlike contemporary colleagues of Rousseau who sentimentalize and romanticize the peasant in painting, he is essentially a folk painter and has the hopes and dreams of the average member of his class.
Rousseau’s obsession with being accepted by the art world is somewhat understandable when evaluated in context: as discussed, he was not only uneducated in the ways of formal painting and began his career at a much older age, but he was producing works at the same time as many other talented and better-known modern artists. Though working for many years already, Rousseau did not begin to receive proper recognition for his art until around the same time that Matisse had begun crafting a reputation as an artist. In the book Modern French Painters, author Jan Gordon asserts that the two, while technically competitors in the art arena, were different not only in style and subject matter but also their reasons for painting in the first place: “Matisse was a painter who conceived a terror of painting in a trite way, while Rousseau’s desire was to paint a picture so conventional that he would be admitted to the Artiste Français” (92).

Many a great thinker has postulated an intimate connection between ethics and aesthetics, between truth and beauty. I believe that at a fundamental level there is a reason for this. As John Keats says in “Ode on a Grecian Urn”, “Beauty is truth, truth beauty- That is all / Ye know on earth, and all ye need to know.” Much of what we know in life is learned via education or experience. However, we seem to appreciate ethics and aesthetics, as Keats implies, without being taught in these expected ways. Both ethics and aesthetics are an attempt to describe rather then prescribe. Our studies of morality and beauty are, for the most part, attempts to explain why a piece of art or literature is beautiful, or why an action is moral, rather than a set of rules for judging, or creating, good art or moral behavior. 
	More to the point, criticism of art or morals is never able to fully capture the essence of what is good or what is beautiful. A conversation about the worth of da Vinci's Mona Lisa, for example, may center around concepts like foreground, background, contrast, or cultural context, but in the end, these do not describe why it is good art. Rather, when one is asked about a favorite work of art or literature it is common to hear a phrase similar to, “There's just something about it” preceding a more complex or critical explanation. I believe that both art and morals can never be completely reduced to a description of their qualities. As Flannery O'Connor says, “A story is a way to say something that can't be said any other way . . . you tell a story because a statement would be inadequate.” No matter how completely we describe the properties of a work of literature, there is something transcendent which is still left.
